    <h2>What is Ground Floor?</h2>
    
    <p>
      Beyond normalizing, but not super-stylized-HTML either:
    </p>
    <p>
      Ground Floor is the prettying up of HTML tags so that even if you never add a single class, or touch a line of CSS your HTML won't look like 
      a jumble of browser presets or bland looking text.
    </p>
    
    <hr />
    
    <h2>HTML Styling</h2>
    <p>
      From headings to tables, forms to HTML5 elements, Ground Floor standardizes and lightly extends basic styling for many HTML elements.
    </p>
